7. How I Made the Program Maintainable, Readable, and Adaptable
I used clear variable names, consistent formatting, and descriptive comments throughout the code. I separated tasks into functions to keep the program modular and easy to update. By avoiding hard‑coded values and keeping the structure flexible, the program can be expanded with new features or redesign options in the future.
